egp x1pg5gke xjb2p0i xo1l8bm xl2ypbo x1ic7a3i" style="--x-fontSize: 12px; --x-lineHeight: 8.5313px; --x-8dd7yt: -0.0137em; --x-hxtmnb: 0.0137em;">Monday</span></div></div><div class="x6s0dn4 x78zum5 x1nxh6w3 x1fc57z9 xr9ek0c xisnujt xhslqc4" data-testid="cell-frame-secondary"><div class="xjbqb8w x1iyjqo2 x1f6kntn x1fc57z9 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1yc453h xlyipyv xuxw1ft xo1l8bm"><span class="x78zum5 x1cy8zhl" title="‪AFFIDAVIT OF GRANTOR/SETTLOR STATUS,
TRUST CREATION, FUNDING AUTHORITY,
AND AUTHORITIES RELIED UPON

STATE OF ARKANSAS

COUNTY OF ______

Before me, the undersigned authority, personally appeared ______________ (&quot;Affiant&quot;), who, after being duly sworn according to law, deposes and states as follows:

────────────────────────────
I. AFFIANT
────────────────────────────

1. I am the Grantor and Settlor of:
   
   ---
   
   (&quot;Trust&quot;)

2. I am of lawful age, competent to testify, and possess personal knowledge of the facts contained herein.

3. This Affidavit is made voluntarily and under oath.

4. This Affidavit is executed to establish a formal record regarding my status as Grantor/Settlor, my authority to establish and fund the Trust, and my relationship to the Trust Estate.

────────────────────────────
II. TRUST CREATION
────────────────────────────

5. I lawfully established the Trust through the execution of a written Trust Agreement.

6. The Trust was created for lawful purposes consistent with applicable law.

7. The Trust presently exists and remains in full force and effect unless amended, revoked, terminated, or otherwise modified according to its governing provisions.

8. The Trust constitutes a fiduciary relationship recognized under the Arkansas Trust Code.

────────────────────────────
III. STATUS OF GRANTOR/SETTLOR
────────────────────────────

9. As Grantor/Settlor, I possess the authority to transfer, assign, convey, and contribute property to the Trust in accordance with the Trust Instrument and applicable law.

10. Property transferred to the Trust becomes subject to the terms and administration of the Trust Agreement.

11. Following transfer, such property may be held by the Trustee in a fiduciary capacity for the benefit of the Trust and its beneficiaries.

12. My status as Grantor/Settlor is legally distinct from the capacities of Trustee, Beneficiary, Protector, Agent, Officer, or any other fiduciary or representative capacity.

13. Unless expressly provided in the Trust Instrument, powers exercised by a Trustee are separate and distinct from powers exercised by a Grantor.

────────────────────────────
IV. TRUST FUNDING AUTHORITY
────────────────────────────

14. I possess authority to contribute assets to the Trust, including but not limited to:

a. Real Property;

b. Personal Property;

c. Financial Accounts;

d. Securities;

e. Business Interests;

f. Intellectual Property;

g. Contracts;

h. Tangible and Intangible Assets;

i. Gifts, Donations, and Contributions.

15. Any property transferred to the Trust shall be governed according to the Trust Instrument and applicable law.

16. Assets conveyed into Trust may thereafter constitute Trust Property and may be administered by the Trustee according to fiduciary duties imposed by law and the governing instrument.

────────────────────────────
V. TRUST RELATIONSHIPS
────────────────────────────

17. Arkansas law recognizes the distinction between legal title and equitable ownership.

18. The Trustee may hold legal title to Trust Property.

19. Beneficiaries may possess equitable interests as provided in the Trust Instrument.

20. The Trust Estate constitutes a separate body of property administered according to the governing instrument.

21. Property held in Trust is distinct from property owned individually by the Trustee or any beneficiary unless otherwise provided by law or the Trust Instrument.

────────────────────────────
VI. RESERVATION OF RIGHTS
────────────────────────────

22. I expressly reserve all rights secured by:

a. The Constitution of the United States;

b. The Constitution of the State of Arkansas;

c. Applicable statutes;

d. Common Law;

e. Equity Jurisprudence;

f. Lawful contracts and agreements.

23. No statement contained herein shall constitute a waiver of any right unless knowingly, voluntarily, and expressly made in writing.

────────────────────────────
VII. AUTHORITIES RELIED UPON
────────────────────────────

24. This Affidavit is made with reference to and reliance upon:

A. Arkansas Constitution

Article 2, Section 2
Inherent and Inalienable Rights

Article 2, Section 3
Equality Before the Law

Article 2, Section 8
Due Process

Article 2, Section 13
Certain Remedy in the Laws

Article 2, Section 21
Protection of Life, Liberty, and Property

Article 2, Section 22
Property Rights

B. Constitution of the United States

Fourth Amendment

Fifth Amendment

Ninth Amendment

Tenth Amendment

Fourteenth Amendment

C. Arkansas Trust Code

Ark. Code Ann. § 28-73-101 et seq.

Ark. Code Ann. § 28-73-103

Ark. Code Ann. § 28-73-401
Methods of Creating Trust

Ark. Code Ann. § 28-73-402
Requirements for Creation

Ark. Code Ann. § 28-73-106
Common Law and Equity Supplement Trust Code

────────────────────────────
VIII. MAXIMS OF LAW AND EQUITY
────────────────────────────

25. The following maxims are cited as interpretive principles:

&quot;Ubi jus ibi remedium.&quot;
(Where there is a right, there is a remedy.)

&quot;Consensus facit legem.&quot;
(Consent makes the law.)

&quot;Qui sentit commodum sentire debet et onus.&quot;
(He who receives the benefit ought also to bear the burden.)

&quot;Ignorantia juris non excusat.&quot;
(Ignorance of the law excuses not.)

&quot;Audi alteram partem.&quot;
(Hear the other side.)

&quot;Nemo judex in causa sua.&quot;
(No one should be a judge in his own cause.)

&quot;Expressio unius est exclusio alterius.&quot;
(The expression of one thing excludes another.)

&quot;Equity regards substance rather than form.&quot;

&quot;Equity regards as done that which ought to be done.&quot;

&quot;He who seeks equity must do equity.&quot;

&quot;He who comes into equity must come with clean hands.&quot;

────────────────────────────
IX. OATH AND VERIFICATION
────────────────────────────

26. I declare under penalty of perjury that the foregoing statements are true and correct to the best of my knowledge and belief.

27. This Affidavit is executed for trust administration, trust funding, banking, property transfers, estate planning, evidentiary purposes, and maintenance of the Trust Record Book.

FURTHER AFFIANT SAYETH NAUGHT.

Executed this __ day of ______, 20.

